Sentencas: High-temperature operation of solid oxide fuel cells causes several degradation and material issues.
Titulo: Semiconductor Fe-doped SrTiO3-δ perovskite electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) operating below 520 °C

Sentencas: Lowering the operating temperature results in reduced fuel cell performance primarily due to the limited ionic conductivity of the electrolyte.
Titulo: Semiconductor Fe-doped SrTiO3-δ perovskite electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) operating below 520 °C

Sentencas: Here we introduce the Fe-doped SrTiO3-delta (SFT) pure perovskite material as an electrolyte, which shows good ionic conduction even at lower temperatures, but has low electronic conduction avoiding short-circuiting.
Titulo: Semiconductor Fe-doped SrTiO3-δ perovskite electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) operating below 520 °C

Sentencas: Fuel cell fabricated using this electrolyte exhibits a maximum power density of 540 mW/cm(2) at 520 degrees C with Ni-NCAL electrodes.
Titulo: Semiconductor Fe-doped SrTiO3-δ perovskite electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) operating below 520 °C

Sentencas: It was found that the Fe-doping into the SrTiO3-delta facilitates the creation of oxygen vacancies enhancing ionic conductivity and transport of oxygen ions.
Titulo: Semiconductor Fe-doped SrTiO3-δ perovskite electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) operating below 520 °C

Sentencas: Such high performance can be attributed to band-bending at the interface of electrolyte/electrode, which suppresses electron flow, but enhances ionic flow.
Titulo: Semiconductor Fe-doped SrTiO3-δ perovskite electrolyte for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) operating below 520 °C
